'''Terado Ōtsuka Kofun''' (寺戸大塚古墳) is a [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]] located in [[:en:Mukō|Muko City]], Terado-cho Shibayama, [[:en:Kyoto Prefecture|Kyoto Prefecture]]. It is part of the {{ill|Otokuni Kofun Cluster|ja|乙訓古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otokuni Kofun Cluster|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135491395}} and is Historic site as a National Historic site.

== Overview ==

The Terado Ōtsuka Kofun is one of the Kofuns in the Mukō Hills Kofun Cluster. It dates back to the middle of the early [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]]. Both the round rear section and the rectangular front section feature {{ill|pit-style stone chambers|ja|竪穴式石室|1=Vertical Pit-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=竪穴式石室|4=zh|5=豎穴式石室|1=Vertical Pit-Style Stone Chamber|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/pit-style stone chambers|13=User:Immanuelle/Vertical Pit-Style Stone Chamber|qq=}}. 

burial goods such as a {{ill|Sankakuen-shinjukyo (triangular-rim deity and beast mirror)|ja|三角縁神獣鏡|1=Triangular-Rimmed Divine Beast Mirror|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sankakuen-shinjukyo (triangular-rim deity and beast mirror)|13=User:Immanuelle/Triangular-Rimmed Divine Beast Mirror|qq=}} found in the mound are believed to have been cast using the same mold as those from [[:en:Tsubai Ōtsukayama Kofun|Tsubai Ōtsukayama Kofun]], suggesting that the buried individual may have been under the control of the leader buried in Tsubai Ōtsukayama Kofun. Currently, much of the front section is eroded due to bamboo grove activity.

The mound's top has an 8 m square plattype surrounded by haniwa (clay cylinders), with the main chamber located directly below. A ceremonial area for haniwa offerings is also present.

== area ==
[[File:Terado Otsuka Kofun, funchou.jpg|thumb|220px|{{center|Top of the rear round section}}]]
[[File:寺戸大塚古墳出土 円筒埴輪 (京都市考古資料館展示).JPG|thumb|200px|right|{{center|Cylindrical Haniwa}}{{small|Photographed during a Kyoto City Archaeological Museum exhibition.}}]]
* Total length: 98 m
* Rear section height: 18 m<ref>[http://www.kyoto-arc.or.jp/News/s-kouza/kouza242.pdf Takao Minami, "Terado Ōtsuka Kofun: Chief's Tomb of the Early Kofun built in Mukō Hills"]</ref>
* Rear section diameter: 57 m

== burial ==
* Front section: A 5.3 m long, approximately 0.9 m wide pit-style stone chamber.
* Rear section: A 6.45 m long, 0.8 m wide, and 1.6 m tall pit-style stone chamber.

